          { question: "Is the taxi equipped for snow in winter?", answer: "Yes, all our vehicles are fitted with winter tyres from November to April. Snow chains are also available for heavy snowfall at Pas de la Case." },
          { question: "How much space for duty-free purchases in the boot?", answer: "Our sedan offers a 500L boot, sufficient for reasonable purchases. For large volumes (spirit cases, electronics), choose our Van with a 1200L cargo area." },
          { question: "Is Pas de la Case often closed in winter?", answer: "The pass can be closed a few days per year during heavy snowfall. The Envalira tunnel (€4) is the alternative. Our drivers check conditions in real time before departure." },
          { question: "Is there a customs check returning from Andorra?", answer: "Yes, French customs conduct random checks at Pas de la Case. Respect legal allowances: 300 cigarettes, 1.5L spirits, 5L wine per person." },
          { question: "Can we stop at Ax-les-Thermes on the way?", answer: "Yes, a stop at Ax thermal baths (Bains du Couloubret, €17) is possible. Allow 1h break. The free open-air Bassin des Ladres is a quick 15 min alternative." }
