        description: "Beziers, a wine city on the banks of the Orb, is 1h40 from Toulouse via the A61 through the Lauragais and Minervois.",
        routeDescription: "The route takes the A61 through the Lauragais, Carcassonne area and Minervois to the gates of Beziers.",
        introduction: "Beziers is one of the oldest cities in France, founded in the 7th century BC by the Greeks. Perched on a promontory overlooking the Orb, it offers a spectacular silhouette dominated by the Cathedral of Saint-Nazaire, a Gothic fortress built after the city's sack during the Albigensian Crusade in 1209 — the tragic episode where the papal legate allegedly declared 'Kill them all, God will recognise His own'. But Beziers is also about southern joie de vivre: the August ferias (bullfights, bodegas, music) attract a million visitors; the Allees Paul-Riquet, a promenade lined with centuries-old plane trees, is the beating heart of the city. The Canal du Midi, masterpiece of Pierre-Paul Riquet (a Beziers native), crosses the city with the famous Fonserannes locks, a nine-basin water staircase listed as UNESCO heritage. The region produces remarkable wines: Faugeres, Saint-Chinian, Minervois, Languedoc. Valras and Serignan beaches are 15 km away. Beziers is a gateway to the Mediterranean Languedoc coast, between vineyards, garrigue and sandy shoreline.",
        itineraire: "From Toulouse, your driver takes the southern ring road then the A61 motorway (Autoroute des Deux Mers) towards Carcassonne. You cross the Lauragais, the historic Land of Cockaigne, with its fields of rapeseed, wheat and sunflowers. The Canal du Midi runs parallel to the motorway — you can spot its rows of plane trees. After Castelnaudary and Carcassonne, the A61 enters the Minervois, a steep wine region where vines grow between garrigue and pine forests. You skirt the Montagne Noire massif on the right before descending to the Beziers plain. At the motorway exit, Beziers appears on its hill with the cathedral as a prow. A61 tolls amount to approximately €15. The journey takes 1h40 under normal conditions. The Narbonne rest area section can slow traffic in summer, especially on Saturday mornings.",
        conseils: "Beziers is best explored on foot from the centre. Start with the Fonserannes locks (free access, easy parking): watching boats navigate the nine basins is fascinating. Walk up to the Cathedral of Saint-Nazaire for the breathtaking view over the wine plain and the Pyrenees on clear days. The Allees Paul-Riquet are perfect for a terrace coffee. On Friday mornings, the grand market on the Allees offers the best of Languedoc produce: Bouzigues oysters, Lucques olives, garrigue honey. For the ferias (mid-August), book your return taxi well ahead as the city is saturated. In summer, Serignan beach (partly naturist) is 15 min away: fine sand, turquoise water. The Riquet Centre retraces the Canal du Midi adventure. Wine lovers should not miss the Faugeres and Saint-Chinian cellars, accessible as a short detour.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Toulouse — Beziers costs €20-28 and takes 1h30 to 2h depending on stops. Trains are fairly frequent (5-7/day) but schedules don't always suit. The Lio/FlixBus costs €5-12 for 2h30-3h. By car, expect €18 in fuel and €15 in tolls. The TaxiNeo taxi at €190 — €250 provides door-to-door service in 1h40, ideal for families with luggage heading to the coast, wine-touring groups going to Minervois or Faugeres, and business travellers. For 4 passengers, the per-person cost (€48-63) is comparable to train plus car rental, with added comfort.",
        faq: [
          { question: "Can we stop at the Fonserannes locks en route?", answer: "Yes, we offer a 15-20 min photo stop at the locks (included). They are at the entrance to Beziers, on the route." },
          { question: "Can the taxi drop me at Valras-Plage or Serignan?", answer: "Yes, supplement of €10-15 for the Beziers coastal beaches (15 km beyond Beziers)." },
          { question: "How much are the Toulouse — Beziers tolls?", answer: "A61 tolls amount to approximately €15, included in the TaxiNeo fixed price." },
          { question: "When are the Beziers ferias?", answer: "The ferias take place mid-August (around 15 August) for 5 days. One million visitors: book well in advance." },
          { question: "Can we visit Faugeres or Saint-Chinian vineyards en route?", answer: "Yes, with our hourly hire option. The Faugeres vineyards are 20 km north of Beziers in stunning schist landscapes." }
        ],
