        conseils: "The Millau Viaduct is impressive from below and above. The viaduct viewing area (dedicated motorway exit) offers a spectacular viewpoint — your driver can stop there. For a panoramic view, climb to the Levezou causse belvedere or the old Millau bridge. Visiting the Roquefort caves is essential: Societe (the largest), Papillon or Gabriel Coulet (more artisanal). The ageing in the natural Combalou fissures, at 11C and 95% humidity, is fascinating. The Tarn Gorges can be paddled by canoe-kayak from La Malene to Hauterives (one day) or by traditional boat (Les Bateliers des Gorges). Paragliding from the Larzac causse above Millau offers unbeatable views of the viaduct and gorges. The Millau market (Friday morning) offers Roquefort, lambskin leather gloves, causse lavender honey, rye bread. Le Bracieux restaurant, in a former townhouse, is the city's gastronomic address.",
        comparaisonTransport: "There is no train to Millau (the station is closed to passengers). The Lio bus costs €2 but takes 3h30 with a change. By car, expect €20 in fuel and €17 in tolls (including viaduct). The TaxiNeo taxi at €220 — €280 is often the only practical option for reaching Millau from Toulouse without a car. Ideal for tourists visiting the viaduct and Tarn gorges, gourmet groups heading to Roquefort caves, and sports enthusiasts (paragliding, canoeing, Causses hiking) with equipment. For 4 passengers, the per-person cost (€55-70) is the only realistic alternative to car rental for this route with no rail service.",
